  body
    .container
      h1.sample-title Seed CSS Framework
      
      p.
        A simple and light-weight mobile first and responsive CSS 
        framework which will help you to start any web site, web app or 
        mobile site.
      
      br
      
    section
      .container
        h2 Container
      
        p Containers are used to define an enclosed area.
      
        .sample-container.align-center .container
        
        .code-sample
          pre.prettyprint.lang-html. 
            &lt;div class="container" &gt;&lt;/div&gt;
          
        hr
    
    section
      .container 
        h2 Grid 
        
        p. 
          Grids are used to define columns. <br >
          The grid system is responsive, which means you can define the number 
          of columns according to the screen size.
        
        .grid.sample
          .row
            .col.sm-12.md-6.lg-3.align-center 
              span .sm-12.md-6.lg-3
            .col.sm-12.md-6.lg-3.align-center 
              span .sm-12.md-6.lg-3
            .col.sm-12.md-6.lg-3.align-center 
              span .sm-12.md-6.lg-3
            .col.sm-12.md-6.lg-3.align-center 
              span .sm-12.md-6.lg-3
        
        .code-sample
          pre.prettyprint.lang-html.
            &lt;div class="grid" &gt;
              &lt;div class="row" &gt;
                &lt;div class="col sm-12 md-6" &gt; ... &lt;/div&gt;
                &lt;div class="col sm-12 md-6" &gt; ... &lt;/div&gt;
              &lt;/div&gt;
            &lt;/div&gt;
        
        p There are up to twelve columns.
        
        .grid.sample
        
          - for (var i=1; i < 12; i++)
            - var j = 12 - i
            - var colA = 'sm-' + i
            - var colB = 'sm-' + j
            .row
              .col.align-center(class=colA)
                span= '.' + colA
              .col.align-center(class=colB)
                span= '.' + colB
              
              
          .code-sample
            pre.prettyprint.lang-html. 
              &lt;div class="grid" &gt;
                &lt;div class="row" &gt;
                  &lt;div class="col sm-1" &gt; ... &lt;/div&gt;
                  &lt;div class="col sm-11" &gt; ... &lt;/div&gt;
                &lt;/div&gt;
              &lt;/div&gt;
          
          .row
            .col.sm-12.align-center 
              span .sm-12
            
          .code-sample
            pre.prettyprint.lang-html.
              &lt;div class="grid" &gt;
                &lt;div class="row" &gt;
                  &lt;div class="col sm-12" &gt; ... &lt;/div&gt;
                &lt;/div&gt;
              &lt;/div&gt;
            
        p. 
          Offsets are also available. <br >
          To apply offsets, just add the sufix <code >-offset</code> to your classname.
        
        .grid.sample
        
          .row
            .col.sm-12.md-6.align-center 
              span .col.sm-12.md-6
          .row
            .col.sm-12.md-6.md-6-offset.align-center 
              span .col.sm-12.md-6.md-6-offset
        
          .code-sample
            pre.prettyprint.lang-html.
              &lt;div class="grid" &gt;
                &lt;div class="row" &gt;
                  &lt;div class="col sm-6" &gt; ... &lt;/div&gt;
                  &lt;div class="col sm-6 sm-6-offset" &gt; ... &lt;/div&gt;
                &lt;/div&gt;
              &lt;/div&gt;
        
        hr

    section
      .container
        h2 Typography
        
        .grid
          .row
            .col.sm-12.md-6
              p.
                All default HTML tags are supported, including but not limited 
                to the below few examples.
              
              p. 
                This is an paragrapher. <br >
                This is a <b >bold</b> text. <br >
                This is an <i >italic</i> text. <br >
                This is an <u >underlined</u> text. <br >
                This is an <a href="#!">anchor</a> text.
                
            .col.sm-12.md-6
              each i in [1,2,3,4,5,6]
                #{'h'+i}= 'Header ' + i
        
        .code-sample
          pre.prettyprint.lang-html.
            &lt;p &gt; ... &lt;/p&gt; 
            &lt;b &gt; ... &lt;/b&gt; 
            &lt;i &gt; ... &lt;/i&gt; 
            &lt;u &gt; ... &lt;/u&gt; 
            &lt;a href="." &gt; ... &lt;/a&gt; 
            
            &lt;h1 &gt; ... &lt;/h1&gt; 
            &lt;h2 &gt; ... &lt;/h2&gt; 
            &lt;h3 &gt; ... &lt;/h3&gt; 
            &lt;h4 &gt; ... &lt;/h4&gt; 
